keywords assassin assassins
---
Assassins are stealth-based melee combatants specializing in precision kills from concealment.
They descend from imperial intelligence agents trained to eliminate targets with minimal disruption.
No formal guild exists. Training passes through small handler-operative chains of one or very few apprentices.
Combat role is single-target elimination. Patience and positioning matter more than raw strength.
Key abilities center on ambush, backstab, and stealth movement.
Practitioners study targets extensively, establish exit routes, and abandon engagements when conditions shift.
The referral chain connects practitioners to clients through informal networks.
Practitioners who compromise discretion are permanently expelled from the chain.
The "perfect kill" doctrine means minimum disruption necessary to achieve the intended outcome.
The Nightblade class synthesizes Assassin precision with Warlock hex and shadow arts.
